{"continue": {"iistart": "2014-11-06T14:05:46Z", "continue": "||"}, "query": {"pages": {"36638808": {"pageid": 36638808, "ns": 6, "title": "File:Darwin Tree 1837.png", "imagerepository": "local", "imageinfo": [{"size": 4423231, "width": 1390, "height": 2265, "canonicaltitle": "File:Darwin Tree 1837.png", "url": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/10/Darwin_Tree_1837.png", "descriptionurl": "https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Darwin_Tree_1837.png", "descriptionshorturl": "https://commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?curid=36638808", "extmetadata": {"DateTime": {"value": "2019-09-25 12:36:00", "source": "mediawiki-metadata", "hidden": ""}, "ObjectName": {"value": "Darwin Tree 1837", "source": "mediawiki-metadata"}, "CommonsMetadataExtension": {"value": 1.2, "source": "extension", "hidden": ""}, "Categories": {"value": "PD-old-70-expired|Phylogenetic trees|CC-PD-Mark|Notebooks by Charles Darwin", "source": "commons-categories", "hidden": ""}, "Assessments": {"value": "", "source": "commons-categories", "hidden": ""}, "ImageDescription": {"value": "<p>Sketch from Charles Darwin's <i>Notebooks on Transmutation of Species</i> (1837), arguably the first example of a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/phylogenetic_tree\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:phylogenetic tree\">phylogenetic tree</a>. (1) represents a common ancestor, the barred branches represent extant descendants, and the unmarked branches represent extinct descendants. The notes read:\n</p>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote language\"><p>I think<br>[sketch]<br>Case must be that one generation then should be as many living as now. To do this &amp; to have many species in same genus (as is) requires extinction.<br>Thus between A &amp; B immense gap of relation, C &amp; B the finest gradation, B &amp; D rather greater distinction. Thus genera would be formed – bearing relation [page break] to ancient types – with several extinct forms[.]\n</p></blockquote>", "source": "commons-desc-page"}, "DateTi